    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exempt disabled people from hotel quarantine once they return from holiday.",
        "additional_details": "There are disabled adults and children's in the UK who have needs which can only be fulfilled if they are at home or at a place where they are familiar with the surroundings. Their health will deteriorate further if they have to quarantine in a single hotel room with limited facilities to what they're normally used to with. \r\n\r\nThere are other disabilities such as autistic or children with development delays where they are registered disabled and need to follow their everyday routine.",
        "background": "Disabled people have various needs which cannot be fulfilled in a hotel room with limited facilities. Being in a single room can deteriorate their health and well being if they quarantine in a hotel room and therefore need to be able to home quarantine once they return from red list countries.",
